# Shovel integration (script-based)

When integrating Shovel into this project, follow `docs/SHOVEL_INTEGRATION.md` (or the Shovel repo copy of that file).

Copy this file to `.cursor/rules/shovel-integration.mdc` in the target repo. Set `alwaysApply: true` in frontmatter to keep it always on.

## Quick reference

**Required files (copy from Shovel repo):**
- `index.js` → serve as static asset (e.g. `public/shovel/index.js`)
- Shovel editor CSS (`.shovel-*` rules from Shovel `styles.css`, section `/* Shovel editor UI */`) → `public/shovel/shovel.css`

**Required wiring:**
```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/shovel/shovel.css" />
<script type="module" src="/shovel/index.js"></script>
```

**Required markup on editable elements:**
```html
data-shovel-source="path/to/file.css:.selector"
data-shovel-tag="button"  <!-- optional -->
```

**Optional config (before script):**
```js
window.__SHOVEL_CONFIG = { repo: "org/repo", baseBranch: "main" };
```

## Rules for agents

1. Shovel boots only when at least one `[data-shovel-source]` exists on the page.
2. `data-shovel-source` format is `<css-file>:<selector>` — selector must exist as a rule in that CSS file.
3. `index.js` does not inject styles — `shovel.css` is mandatory.
4. Only enable on staging/local (`SHOVEL_STAGING=true`), never production.
5. No npm package — copy `index.js` and CSS from the Shovel repo.
6. For React/Vue, add `data-shovel-source` manually on rendered elements (or use `@shovel/vite-plugin` from Shovel `tooling/` for auto-stamping).

## Verification

- Console: `[Shovel] Editor ready — click any element or the shovel button to start.`
- ⛏ button appears bottom-right, styled
- Clicking stamped element opens editor + live CSS preview
